SIMPLE: hornbook
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hornbook
<hw>Horn"book`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
first book for children, or that from which in former times they learned
their letters and rudiments; -- so called because a sheet of horn
covered the small, thin board of oak, or the slip of paper, on which the
alphabet, digits, and often the Lord's Prayer, were written or printed;
a primer.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧He teaches boys the <xex>hornbook</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A book containing the rudiments of any science or
branch of knowledge; a manual; a handbook.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornbug</ent>⟦br⟧
